summary: Didn't think I'd finish Killing Eve in one sitting but I got thru all 8 episodes before my shift ended. I enjoyed it, too. It's...
body: Didn’t think I’d finish Killing Eve in one sitting but I got thru all 8 episodes before my shift ended. I enjoyed it, too. It’s kind of a cat-and-mouse chase but both the cat and the mouse are obsessed with one another; at first impressed and then straight up crushing. And the two main characters are such a step up from the usual detective and criminal typecast so you get invested in both sides of the chase. It’s a quick watch and the leads give amazing performances. Sandra Oh definitely earned her Supporting Actress Golden Globe. I say give it a watch.
